<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - LIGHT SYSTEMS - TROUBLESHOOTING - Headlight
        System With Signal-Stat Turn Signal Switch, Push Button Dimmer Switch, Without DRL and International Engine
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Headlight System With Signal-Stat Turn Signal Switch, Push Button Dimmer Switch, Without DRL and
            International Engine
        </title>
        <table id="t0824014" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Headlight System With Signal-Stat Turn Signal Switch, Push Button Dimmer Switch, Without DRL and
                International Engine
            </title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.54in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.54in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.69in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.78in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.74in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.56in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove fuse F26 and check for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>F26.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re-install fuse F26, and at circuit 14F measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>F26, 14F to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 14F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (35) and at circuit 50, measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(35), 50 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 50, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bench test headlight switch (35) by placing switch in headlight on position, and
                                measuring resistance from term. 1 to 2.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(35), term. 1 to 2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective headlight switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (17) and reconnect connector (35). With headlight switch still
                                on, measure voltage at (17) from circuit 51F to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(17), 51F to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 51F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remove fuse F7 and check for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>F7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Re-install fuse F7, and at circuit 14A measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>F7, 14A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 14A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remove relay (276) and at circuit 50E measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(276), 50E to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 50E or 63, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (421) and at circuit 52-GA, measure resistance to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(421), 52-GA to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 52-GA or 11-G, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Test push button dimmer switch by placing in dim position and measuring resistance at
                                conn. (421), from white wire to white wire.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(421), white wire to white wire.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Test push button dimmer switch by placing in bright position and measuring resistance
                                at conn. (421), from white wire to white wire.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(421), white wire to white wire.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Replace defective switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Reconnect connector (421) and with dimmer switch in bright position, at relay socket
                                (276) and circuit 51-GA, measure resistance to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(276), 51-GA to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 51-GA, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (17) and at relay socket (276), with headlight switch in headlight
                                position, measure voltage from circuit 51B to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(276), 51B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 51B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Bench test dimmer relay (276) by measuring resistance from terminal 30 to 87A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Relay (276), term. 30 to 87A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Replace defective relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Bench test dimmer relay (276) by applying +12V to terminal 85, ground to terminal 86,
                                and measuring resistance from terminal 30 to 87.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Energized relay (276), term. 30 to 87.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Replace defective relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>16.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (17), re-install dimmer relay (276), and place dimmer switch in dim
                                position. At (17), measure resistance from circuit 51B to 53D.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(17), 51B to 53D.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 53D, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>17.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Place dimmer switch in bright position and at (17), measure resistance from circuit
                                51B to 52D.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(17), 51B to 52D.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 52D, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>18.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (2) and reconnect (17). With headlight switch in headlight
                                position and dimmer switch in dim position, at (2), measure voltage from circuit 53 to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(2), 53 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 53 or 53B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>19.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (502) and (504) and reconnect (2). With switches still set, at
                                (502), measure voltage from circuit 53B to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(502), 53B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 53 or 53B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>20.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (504) with switches still set, measure voltage from circuit 53A to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(504), 53A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 53A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>21.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At connector (502) with switches still set, measure voltage from circuit 53B to
                                11-GC.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(502), 53B to 11-GC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 11-GB or 11-GC, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>22.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (504) with switches still set, measure voltage from circuit 53A to 11-GE.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(504), 53A to 11-GE.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 11-GB or 11-GE, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>23.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect connector (2). Move headlight switch to headlight position and dimmer
                                switch to bright position. Measure voltage from circuit 52 to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(2), 52 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 52 or 52F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>24.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With connectors (502) and (504) still disconnected and switches still set, reconnect
                                conn. (2) and at (502) measure voltage from circuit 52C to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(502), 52C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 52 or 52C, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>25.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With switches still set, at (504) measure voltage from circuit 52B to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(504), 52B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Head- light circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 52B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
